extendedInfo.description: This key unlocks premium features of free PrinterShare application. It cannot be used on its own! If you haven't done so already, please install main free PrinterShare app and print test page before purchasing this key.With PrinterShare Mobile Print you can instantly print Office documents, bills and invoices (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, PDF, text files and more) directly from your tablet or phone (from internal memory, SD card or cloud source such as Google Drive / Google Docs) to a printer right next to you or anywhere in the world!You can also print emails from Gmail, print photos and images (JPG, PNG, GIF), print contacts, agenda, sms/mms, call log, web pages (HTML) and other digital content. You may configure many print options including paper size, page orientation, number of copies, page range, one- or two-sided printing (duplex mode), print quality (resolution), printout mode (color or monochrome), output tray and more.Premium Features:* Nearby direct printing via Wi-Fi, Bluetooth and USB without PC;* Nearby printing to Windows shared (SMB/CIFS) or Mac shared printers;* Unlimited Remote printing. The receiving end (Windows or Mac) would not have to buy pages or subscribe.Note: Main PrinterShare app also supports Google Cloud Print service at no charge.PrinterShare are supporting a wide variety of HP, Epson, Canon, Brother, Samsung, Kodak, Dell, Lexmark and other printers including legacy networkable.Have a good print!

reviews.title: Excellent
reviews.comment: I need to print from usb from my Galaxy Note 10.1 and this works perfectly.  I would like to be able to center documents on a page and to scale them.  Could the margin size be increased?  Perhaps this is in progress.  Never the less, this app is a real work horse.
reviews.author: David Tan Creti

reviews.title: Direct via USB. Perfect 1st go
reviews.comment: Using Sony Xperia Acro whilst connected to TV [desk] with bluetooth mouse and keyboard. PC getting closer to bin every day. Printed direct to loved old HP DJ 930c.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Never a minute\'s problem
reviews.comment: You just want a program like this to work. It works.  Every time.  It has just enough options to be helpful. Great job.

reviews.title: What I\'ve been looking for.
reviews.comment: Great app... printing is easy over wireless LAN using Samsung Note. Just check your printer is on the list of printers supported. If so, install,  test and pay and you are printing.

reviews.title: PrinterShare Premium
reviews.comment: This application is invaluable....I can finally print documents from my Android tablet.  As a recommendation to the software developers can I suggest you include A4 to the list of paper sizes on offer with the next update.
reviews.author: Kim Parkin

reviews.title: Excellent
reviews.comment: Delivers in a smooth,  reliable manner. Great app!

reviews.title: Great!

reviews.title: Super easy
reviews.comment: Love my printer share. Use it from my android phone and tabled. Never a problem and I can print anywhere wireless printers are!

reviews.title: Great App! Makes my smartphone even Smarter
reviews.comment: Love the PS app. Only wish it would print from all of my email apps, seems to only print gmail.      Would give it 5 \342\230\205\'s except for this shortcomimg.
reviews.author: Vurl Bland

reviews.title: Finally a print app  that works
reviews.comment: A little complex in my case since my Canon Imageclass MF4890dw and my HP Officejet J4860 were not on the list of directly supported printers.  However, PrinterShare allows web passthru to my printers defined on my Windows 7 laptop using a special PrinterShare application installed on the PC.  Now that its set up, it works beautify to either of my printers.  Compared to how printers are integrated in all your applications on a PC, it takes a little getting used to to go into PrintShare first and then enter their sub-apps to actually print your email or your webpage etc.  None-the-less, it is wonderful to be able to finally print things from my ASUS Android tablet.
reviews.author: Byron Nate

reviews.title: Good but...
reviews.comment: Good software. Would gladly give 5 stars if I could print from my mail droid app. Please fix...
reviews.author: Mark Bates

reviews.title: Don\'t bother.
reviews.comment: Bought a new Samsung ml 2165 laser printer. 3 months later and still no driver and you lot have the cheek to charge considerable amounts of money for an app that is very rarely updated. Waste of time and money.

reviews.title: Work great
reviews.comment: I have been using this app on note2 and the note tablet. It finds the printers on a network and prints flawlessly.  Great job

reviews.title: Works
reviews.comment: Tested on HP p1102w. Works. What let\'s down this app is the price. Yes their are similar apps that print through Google print, but AFAIK this is the only app in existence that prints direct without eprint or Google print. I give 3 star rating because of the expensive price.

reviews.title: Very handy n good
reviews.comment: Works like a charm with Samsung galaxy note 2  Auto driver installation is good.  Now I can print easily from anywhere in office without laptop. However I m giving it 4 stars because its not working with other mail clients like yahoo etc. It should give print option in menu of all mail, message or document related pages or application we open.

reviews.title: Awesome App.
reviews.comment: I\'m able to print to a usb joined HP1200 on my network with my Asus SL101 and my HTC EVO 4G 3D.  I am much more productive..  I can also print while I\'m away from the house and have t waiting on me when I get home.  If you haven\'t tried it, I would highly suggest it. I love it so much that I purchased the Pro version.  Happy Apping to you!

reviews.title: Technical support is great
reviews.comment: I have some issues printing using a bluetooth so I geve lower rating but I got contacted by a technical team the next day so I have to say it was surprisingly good I\'ll definitely give 5 stars after the problem is solved

reviews.title: Nexus 7 (2013) + Canon MP495 - Performed as expected.
reviews.comment: Tested on an email text message, printed the text as expected, as text. Also tried a web page with graphics and an image. The jpeg was smaller than expected, but otherwise performed as expected.  I saw the comments on price. I would have rather paid $8 instead of $12, but given no other comparable choice for the Canon, I am pleased.  My opinion is that a device that cannot print is very handicapped.
reviews.author: Garry Porterfield

reviews.title: Still has some bugs
reviews.comment: Crashes and restarts when rendering photos prior to selecting print or if it does render them it will crash when selecting options. It will sometimes lose my selected printer when this happens. Nexus7 Jellybean 4.2
